HOUSE RESOLUTION 293
By Pearson
A RESOLUTION to honor Johnnie Mosley for his distinguished
leadership and service as Founding Chairman of
Citizens for Better Service and to commend the
advocacy of the Memphis Bus Riders Union.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that we should recognize those citizens who have devoted
themselves to improving the quality of life for their communities through advocacy, leadership,
and a steadfast commitment to justice; and
WHEREAS, Johnnie Mosley, as the Founding Chairman of Citizens for Better Service,
established in 1993, has demonstrated a lifelong dedication to ensuring equitable access to
essential public services, particularly for underserved and marginalized communities; and
WHEREAS, through his visionary leadership, Mr. Mosley has worked tirelessly to amplify
the voices of everyday citizens, advocating for fairness, accountability, and improved public
infrastructure, thereby uplifting countless individuals and families throughout Memphis and
beyond; and
WHEREAS, his commitment to civic engagement and grassroots organizing has inspired
a new generation of leaders to continue the work of building stronger, more just, and more
equitable communities; and
WHEREAS, the Memphis Bus Riders Union has served as a vital force in advocating for
accessible, reliable, and affordable public transportation for the residents of Memphis; and
WHEREAS, the Memphis Bus Riders Union has brought attention to the critical role that
public transit plays in economic opportunity, workforce access, and community connectivity,
ensuring that the voices of transit-dependent riders are heard and respected; and
HR0293
018682
- 1 -

WHEREAS, through persistent organizing, public engagement, and advocacy, the
Memphis Bus Riders Union has championed improvements to transit services and equity in
transportation policy, standing as a model of grassroots activism and civic responsibility; and
WHEREAS, the collective efforts of Johnnie Mosley and organizations such as the
Memphis Bus Riders Union exemplify the power of community-led advocacy in advancing
justice and equity across the State of Tennessee; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, that we honor and
commend Johnnie Mosley for his outstanding service as Founding Chairman of Citizens for
Better Service and extend our deep appreciation for his enduring contributions to the people of
the State of Tennessee.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy.
